  "response": "The iPhone 6s Plus was developed by Apple Inc. and was released in September 2015. It featured several key design and technological improvements over its predecessor, including:\n\n1. Materials and Design\n- Aluminum body with a slightly thicker design compared to iPhone 6 Plus\n- Introduction of Rose Gold color option\n- Maintained similar overall form factor of previous model\n\n2. Technological Innovations\n- Introduction of 3D Touch pressure-sensitive display technology\n- A9 chip with improved processing power\n- Upgraded 12-megapixel rear camera\n- Improved front-facing camera with 5-megapixel sensor\n\n3. Development Process\n- Led by Apple's design team under Chief Design Officer Jony Ive\n- Focused on incremental improvements to previous model\n- Extensive research and testing of new technologies like 3D Touch\n\nThe development would have involved multiple teams at Apple collaborating on hardware, software, design, and manufacturing aspects. However, specific internal details of the development process are not publicly disclosed by Apple.\n\nThis summary reflects generally known information about the iPhone 6s Plus's design and development based on public sources.",
